Mons den ul van 8 deser over Rijssel ontfangen, dogh den
orginelen van 5 ditto waer dan vors de copie behelft en is
mij niet geworden waer over verwondert ben en het selve
doet mij vreesen dat den luck niet wel sal sijn gevediteert
venwel ick hebbe monsr van de keninck gesproken die wende
van de remisse niet te betalen waer laken imant anders die
mij geirne ad gehregen soo dat hier geen weeirde daer voor sal
betalt worden ten waere den brief te reghte quam, hepe ul
den selven nogh in tijts sal hebben geinteriieert, soo niet sal die
aen ul te nigh seynden, soo haest den selven mij ter tant comt &
niet weijdens daer in ageeren

refaexne aen & de larre gecort heb ul gedelit voor t montant van de

Lille mr. Richard Sanhell
mij last to you was mtle q pur. to wilh which neferre you, according
to my advise ther is m. Collier Gou fromthence yeasterday, so that I hipe
de will be with you this day, Incloted ae pad. of his resting clooth
excost one pay, which as in the prets, if yu could sill tle lestt coullours
I could make shift with the rest, though I do not care if all could
sell with you, I have the lede which d. whiting brought fhom duynckere
I am forry to see the contents, I have not recd. the leder of m. willing too with
dis remise, so save desired ohat de cominch not to pay to any other, if the bill was
miscarried, I have wrot as much this day to uynckerese. I hav sent yeasterday
a laden for m. Colliur after him which I reed from luyd, I have dinceted itt to
ft: Herrebout to dibider sim yeasterday evening, which I hope te hade reed, so
please to acquant u will itt, for nt was vam dis som, & as I persecaved
conr. much uniting. I wonder you do not artunermy bill on yay which I expect
